    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.34,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 3.18,
      "end": 5.32,
      "text": "All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.24,
      "end": 12.3,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org, recorded by Andrew Sorsini,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 13.16,
      "end": 16.76,
      "text": "Asop's fables, the mouse, the frog, and the hawk.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.5,
      "end": 19.92,
      "text": "A mouse and a frog struck up a friendship.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 20.66,
      "end": 24.72,
      "text": "They were not well-mated for the mouse lived entirely on land while the frog was equally",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 24.72,
      "end": 26.54,
      "text": "at home on land or in the water.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 27.1,
      "end": 30.92,
      "text": "In order that they might never be separated, the frog tied himself and the mouse together",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 30.92,
      "end": 32.94,
      "text": "by the leg with a piece of thread.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 33.52,
      "end": 36.4,
      "text": "As long as they kept on dry land, all went fairly well.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 37.04,
      "end": 41.66,
      "text": "But coming to the edge of a pool, the frog jumped in, taking the mouse with him, and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 41.66,
      "end": 43.94,
      "text": "began swimming about and croaking with pleasure.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 44.98,
      "end": 49.78,
      "text": "The unhappy mouse, however, was soon drowned and floated about on the surface in the wake",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 49.78,
      "end": 50.28,
      "text": "of the frog.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 51.02,
      "end": 56.04,
      "text": "There he was spied by a hawk who pounced down on him and seized him in his talons.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 56.86,
      "end": 62.08,
      "text": "The frog was unable to loose the knot which bound him to the mouse, and thus was carried",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 62.08,
      "end": 64.68,
      "text": "off along with him and eaten by the hawk.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 65.76,
      "end": 68.62,
      "text": "End of the mouse, the frog, and the hawk.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
